<question-stem>
<para> What does the professor say Hawaii should do to save its seals?<mediaExhibit
frameType="mp3" mediaRef="toeflPrac10220.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> Exchange more scientific data with researchers
in Florida</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Begin a research program to learn as much as possible about
the habitat needs of monk seals</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Educate the public to prevent further poaching of monk seals</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Consider Florida's experience with monk seals a warning of
what could happen in Hawaii</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The professor says that Hawaiian monk seals are endangered, probably
for similar reasons the Caribbean monk seals became extinct in Florida: tourism
and rapid, uncontrolled development. So (D) is the correct choice. Though
they are logical, (A), (B), and (C) are never mentioned as ways to save Hawaii's
seals.</para>
</explanation>
